@node intro "Introduction"

CheckDownloads is a little program that uses VirusZ to check archives
in a dir. I wrote it because a friend wanted a script where new archives
from Aminet are checked with VirusZ. So I wrote this script. For more
informations see @{"What does it" link work}!

@endnode

@node req "Requierements"

You need:
- VirusZ
- RexxMast running
- Rexxreqtools.library
- Rexxtricks.library
- Aminet archives ;)
- A dir where all your aminet downloads are saved to

@endnode

@node install "Installation"

Copy it where you want and start CheckDownloadsConfig.rexx.

It's recommend that you start CheckDownloads, when you go offline.
I've made a entry in Miami/Events/Quit.
My entry:
"rx CheckDownloads".

@endnode

@node config "Configuration"

I have written a config program for CheckDownloads, it's called
"CheckDownloadsConfig.rexx". Start it by typing in a shell:
"rx CheckDownloadsConfig.rexx". (You should be in the dir, where
CheckDownloadsConfig.rexx is located :))

Then follow these steps:
1. Select the VirusZ executeable.
   (e.g. "Work:VirusZ/VirusZ")
2. Select the dir, where all your Aminet downloads are saved to.
   (e.g. "DH0:Downloads/")
3. Select if VirusZ should be quitted after checking.
   This is useful, if VirusZ don't runs in the background and
   you just want to start it for checking. If you select "Yes",
   VirusZ will be started at checking (if not already running) and
   after checking VirusZ will be quitted.
4. Now enter the english word "Today" in the language your WB is.
   (for example your WB is german, you would have to enter "Heute")
   This is used for the list command.
5. At last select your language. At this time only english and german
   are supported.

That's all.

@endnode

@node use "Usage"

As I said in the installation chapter, it's recommend that you start
CheckDownloads when you go offline. I've made a entry in
Miami/Events/Quit, it's called "rx CheckDownloads". This will start
CheckDownloads, when you quit Miami.
The Usage is simply. Just start it and it will check your download
dir, that you have configured. If the archives are ok, no message
will appear and VirusZ will be quitted, if you have configured that
VirusZ should be quitted after checking. If a virus is found, a
requester will appear, that tells you the name of the archive and
checking will be proceeded. When the check is done, the names of
the archives, that contain a virus are written to RAM:Virfile.

@endnode

@node work "How does it work?"

Well, at first it starts VirusZ, if it isn't already running. Then
it makes a list with all archivenames that are in your download
dir, with the help of the AmigaDOS list command. Only the archives
that contain "Today" in the date string are taken on this list.
Because this you had to type the translation of "today" in the
config program. Then it loads these list and tells VirusZ that
it should check these archives. If viriies a requester will appear
and the name of this archive will be written into a file in RAM:
called "Virfile". If viriies are found, CheckDownloads will ignore
the configs for quitting VirusZ. If the archives are ok,
CheckDownloads will quit without any message.

@endnode

